              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma rays from the 2+ to 0+ de-excitation of",
                " the first excited state in 12C were observed in",
                " coincidence with inelastically scattered neutrons.",
                "Background was minimized by requiring coincidence",
                " between the neutrons and the associated alpha-",
                " particles"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight technique was necessary to",
                " distinguish neutron-gamma from gamma-neutron events.",
                "Measurements were performed in the reaction plane for",
                " five different neutron detector positions and in a",
                " plane perpendicular to the reaction plane for two",
                " neutron detector positions."
              ]
            }
          ],
